        "text": "## Cu²⁺–EDTA: Highest log K — Original Publication\n\nThe highest reported log K for the 1:1 Cu²⁺–EDTA complex in SRD-46 is **log K = 18.78**, measured at 25 °C and ionic strength I = 0.1 M (reaction: Cu²⁺ + EDTA⁴⁻ ⇌ [Cu(EDTA)]²⁻, `beta_def_812`, VLM ID: `vlm_108604`).\n\n| Parameter | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| log K | **18.78** |\n| Temperature | 25 °C |\n| Ionic Strength | 0.1 M |\n| Species | [Cu(EDTA)]²⁻ (1:1 ML) |\n| VLM ID | vlm_108604 |\n| SRD-46 citation shortcut | 58Sc |",
